  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>When a person first arrives on OpenHatch.org, they see the beautiful landing page that clearly 
states what the site does and links to all of the useful features. However, once the user logs in to 
OH, they cannot return to that useful landing page anymore unless they log out again, which 
makes the site a bit more confusing and difficult to navigate while logged in.

I propose that the initial landing page should have a different URL from the user's "home" page 
when logged in, and you should be able to access the initial landing page while logged in. 
Perhaps "home" should give the user their personal homepage, while clicking the OpenHatch logo 
takes them to the landing page.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
